      • addNamespaceAliasMapping

        private void addNamespaceAliasMapping(String targetNamespace,
                                      String namespaceAlias,
                                      String namespaceURI)
        Add a new map entry for an alias and the namespace of the library that it references. Mappings are scoped according to the namespace of the model (default RAML / library) that is being initialised.
        Parameters:
        targetNamespace - The namespace of the default OpenAPI or library whose types are being processed.
        namespaceAlias - The alias from the uses list that is used to reference a library.
        namespaceURI - The namespace URI derived from the referenced library.

      • initialiseTypeMap

        private void initialiseTypeMap(com.reprezen.kaizen.oasparser.model3.OpenApi3 model,
                               String targetNamespaceURI,
                               Set<String> visitedModelSet)
        Recursively initialise the type map. Libraries may be specified multiple times with different aliases, and all aliases are mapped. The recursive processing of libraries considers each one once in any scope, and skips it if it encounters it again during the recursive initialisation process.
        Parameters:
        model - The model built from parsing the OpenAPI.
        targetNamespaceURI - The target namespace URI for the model being processed.
        visitedModelSet - The set of types that have been visited (to guard against infinite recursion).

      • prepareComplexType

        private org.eclipse.xtext.xbase.lib.Pair<org.apache.ws.commons.schema.XmlSchemaComplexType,Boolean> prepareComplexType(String namespaceURI,
                                                                                                                       String typeName,
                                                                                                                       OASType oasType,
                                                                                                                       SchemaVisitorContext context)
        Using an enclosing namespace, a type name, and a type declaration, attempt to lookup an existing type map entry that may or may not contain a constructed XML schema type object. If a type entry is found then the specified type declaration is compared with the type declaration in the type map entry to determine whether the type is a reference to a top level type or is a subclass that extends a top level type. For type references, the XML schema type is returned from the type map entry. For a subclass, the method creates a new XmlSchemaComplexType object. If there is no type map entry then the type is not found and null is returned.
        Parameters:
        namespaceURI - The enclosing namespace for the complex type.
        typeName - The type name.
        oasType - The type declaration.
        context - The visitor context.
        Returns:
        Pair.of(XmlSchemaComplexType, Boolean), or Pair.of(null, false) if type is anonymous or type declarations are not equal.

      • prepareComplexTypeAnnotation

                                                                                      SchemaVisitorContext context)

        Parameters:

        Returns:

      • prepareArrayType

        private org.eclipse.xtext.xbase.lib.Pair<XmlSchemaArrayType,Boolean> prepareArrayType(String namespaceURI,
                                                                                      String typeName,
                                                                                      OASType oasType,
                                                                                      SchemaVisitorContext context)
        Using an enclosing namespace, a type name, and a type declaration, attempt to lookup an existing type map entry that may or may not contain a constructed XML schema type object. If a type entry is found then the specified type declaration is compared with the type declaration in the type map entry to determine whether the type is a reference to a top level type or is a subclass that extends a top level type. For type references, the XML schema type is returned from the type map entry. For a subclass, the method creates a new XmlSchemaArrayType object. If there is no type map entry then the type is anonymous and null is returned.
        Parameters:
        namespaceURI - the enclosing namespace for the array type
        typeName - the type name
        oasType - the type definition
        context - the visitor context
        Returns:
        Pair.of(XmlSchemaArrayType, Boolean), or Pair.of(null, false) if type is not found or type declarations are not equal
